docs.abstract: Turkish Pres Tayyip Recep Erdogan's insistence on playing role in battle to retake city of Mosul from Islamic State has been met with alarm and resistance from Iraqi government, creating dispute that complicates already fraught operation; Turkey has already angered Iraq and undermined its sense of sovereignty by stationing troops within its borders without permission.

docs.abstract: Law enforcement and computer security experts caution it is only matter of time before artificial intelligence will be used by criminals, given how advanced the technology is becoming; particularly worrisome is growing use of customer service chatbots that could be exploited by criminals to manipulate people into divulging private information or performing some questionable action.
